Step-by-Step Commands

Here are the clean, copy-pasteable terminal blocks corresponding to each step above:
STEP 1 Command
Bash

uname -r && pacman -Q | grep -E "linux|headers"

STEP 2 Command
Bash

lspci -k | grep -A 3 -E "VGA|3D"

STEP 3 Command
Bash

nvidia-smi

STEP 4 Command
Bash

env | grep -E "XDG_SESSION_TYPE|WAYLAND"

STEP 5 Command
Bash

prime-run glxinfo | grep "OpenGL renderer"

STEP 6 Command
Bash

systemctl suspend
# (Wake system up, then run:)
sudo dmesg | grep -i nvidia
